{"id":592,"date":"2018-07-27T20:21:58","date_gmt":"2018-07-27T20:21:58","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/?p=592"},"modified":"2018-07-27T20:21:58","modified_gmt":"2018-07-27T20:21:58","slug":"adjusting-cards-part-two","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-two\/","title":{"rendered":"Adjusting Cards (part two)"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Hello everyone! Today I thought I would write a bit about the adjustments I have made recently to the Sophomore deck. These mainly consist of small action point buffs to make Sophomore year a lot less difficult. There is some history to a very difficult Sophomore year: at my high school, it is considered the toughest year out of all of them. That was definitely reflected in earlier versions of the game, but even in later versions Sophomore year was always unusually tough as the average action point value didn&#8217;t differ much from the Freshman year deck.<\/p>\n<p>Right now, an event card from the Sophomore deck has an average action point value of 2.81 (compared to Freshman year 2.48), giving players around 14 actions. It takes 15 Stats to correct all Sophomore classes to an A (compared to freshman year 9 stats and 12.4 actions). So, Sophomore year is still tough, it just hopefully won&#8217;t be as difficult as before!<\/p>\n<p>These are the cards that were changed:<\/p>\n<p>Copying Lab Reports<\/p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"444\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/event-cards-next-steps\/copying-lab-reports\/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports.png?fit=240%2C336&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"240,336\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Copying Lab Reports\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports.png?fit=240%2C336&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-444\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports.png?resize=242%2C339&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"242\" height=\"339\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports.png?w=240&amp;ssl=1 240w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 242px) 100vw, 242px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><img data-attachment-id=\"593\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-two\/copying-lab-reports-2\/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?fit=1000%2C1400&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1000,1400\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Copying Lab Reports\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?fit=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-593\" src=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?resize=243%2C340&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"243\" height=\"340\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?w=1000&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?resize=768%2C1075&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Copying-Lab-Reports-1.png?resize=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 243px) 100vw, 243px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p>This card was buffed to make the Science stat increase from +1 to +3. I think that this card was always a little underwhelming since losing an Integrity is a pretty significant cost for a card only worth 2 actions and a Science stat. This change makes the card a lot stronger, but also without the same flexibility of a card worth 5 action points.<\/p>\n<p>Doubts<\/p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"428\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/event-cards-next-steps\/doubts\/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts.png?fit=240%2C336&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"240,336\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Doubts\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts.png?fit=240%2C336&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-428\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts.png?resize=241%2C337&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"241\" height=\"337\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts.png?w=240&amp;ssl=1 240w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 241px) 100vw, 241px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><img data-attachment-id=\"594\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-two\/doubts-2\/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?fit=1000%2C1400&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1000,1400\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Doubts\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?fit=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-594\" src=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?resize=239%2C335&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"239\" height=\"335\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?w=1000&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?resize=768%2C1075&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Doubts-1.png?resize=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 239px) 100vw, 239px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Doubts was always a terrible card, giving only 2 Action Points for a cost of 2 Happiness. One Happiness is roughly worth one Action Point because you can use Hesling to convert chats to Happiness, and so counting that way this card was basically worthless. Post buffs, there are only 5 cards in the Sophomore deck worth 4 Action points, so it is indeed much more playable now.<\/p>\n<p>A note about worthless cards. Before, my thought on them was that &#8220;bad cards&#8221; should exist in order to encourage players to use the Graff ability, or use cards as discard fodder. However, I think that while cards should vary in quality, it is also important to make sure that cards give some benefit in order to create more difficult decisions. If there are cards that are just objectively terrible, then the choice between using the card and trading it away is lost.<\/p>\n<p>Progress Reports<\/p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"424\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/event-cards-next-steps\/progress-reports\/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports.png?fit=240%2C336&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"240,336\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Progress Reports\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports.png?fit=240%2C336&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-424\" src=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports.png?resize=243%2C341&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"243\" height=\"341\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports.png?w=240&amp;ssl=1 240w, https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 243px) 100vw, 243px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><img data-attachment-id=\"595\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-two\/progress-reports-2\/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?fit=1000%2C1400&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1000,1400\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Progress Reports\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?fit=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-595\" src=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?resize=242%2C339&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"242\" height=\"339\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?w=1000&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w, https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?resize=768%2C1075&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Progress-Reports-1.png?resize=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 242px) 100vw, 242px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p>While this card does attack other players, I&#8217;ve found that it is difficult to get significant value out of this card. If you wait to play it until you have corrected a few of your classes to As, chances are, other players have caught up too. Playing it immediately is also tough since it basically just gives all players 4 Stress. Thus, I think that this card seems better than it really is and deserved a small buff.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Offensive Social Media Post<\/p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"437\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/event-cards-next-steps\/offensive-social-media-post\/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?fit=240%2C336&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"240,336\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quo